The groups believe that Police Minister Nkosinathi Nhleko shouldn't have appointed Ntlemeza on the basis that he is not fit to hold office. JOHANNESBURG - Freedom Under Law and the Helen Suzman Foundation are arguing that Hawks head Berning Ntlemeza's appointment was irrational.The High Court in Pretoria is hearing an application brought by the civil rights group today, several months after it ruled that the matter is not urgent.The groups believe that Police Minister Nkosinathi Nhleko shouldn't have appointed Ntlemeza on the basis that he is not fit to hold office.Freedom Under Law's Nicole Fritz explains: &quot;There have been clear pronouncements by the high court that he is unbiased, a dishonest person, lacking integrity and has an attitude towards the rule of law. On this basis we argue he is not fit and proper for this high office. The decision to appoint him must be reviewed and set aside.&quot;(Edited by Shimoney Regter)